result.execSummary:
The defendant James A Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
The defendant may not consume or possess alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns.

The defendant must undergo an anger management assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must submit a DNA sample.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

Defendant James A Jones in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Defendant James A Jones in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:00 AM. State - resolved - dismiss and read in count #1, amend count 2 to DC contrary to 947.01 and plead to cont #3 as alleged, joint recommendation of a withheld sentence on each count, place on probation for 1 year with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, anger management and follow thru, no consumption or possession and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 50 hours of community service - have complied with victim notification requirements. Court dismisses and reads in count #1. Court amends count to to DC contrary to 947.01. Jones pleads G to count #2 as amended and #3 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Voorhees makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Defendant's father makes a statement. Jones makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #2 and #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 1 year, concurrent to each other, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, anger management and follow thru, no consumption or possession and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 50 hours of community service, costs on each count - 60 DTP/CO, credit for 19 days only if revoked, submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant James A Jones in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Defendant James A Jones in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Called at 10:31 AM. State asks Court to take notice that the defendant was out on bond from Langlade County Case #16CF122. Voorhees has no objections to that. Court takes judicial notice that the defendant is charged in Langlade County Case #16CF122 for purposes of felony bail jumping today. State provides exhibit #1 - signed bond for FC Case #16CM105. Court receives exhibit #1 after no objections. State calls Deputy Chris Tanner. Tanner sworn in at 10:35 AM. Direct exam by State. Record reflects proper identification of the defendant (10:38 AM). Cross exam by Voorhees at 10:41 AM. State objects - beyond scope - sustained (10:42 AM). Tanner excused at 10:43 AM. State calls Kyle Plamer. Palmer sworn in at 10:43 AM. Direct exam by State. Cross exam by Voorhees at 10:45 AM. Palmer excused at 10:46 AM. Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed, binds over for trial. State files Information that mirrors the complaint. State needs clarification of the defendant's address for stated reasons. Voorhees has Information but would like to talk to his client regarding his right to substitute. Recess at 10:48 AM. Recalled at 11:17 AM with same appearances. Voorhees has gone over the Information with the defendant, waives further reading, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court will set both matters for FPT, 16CM105 will tag along with. Voorhees - bond - asks for reduction in bond and add condition of participate in AODA treatment for stated reasons. State - bond - victims have informed him that they do not wany any contact with the defendant and believe he needs help, wants bond to continue. State - 16CM105 was set for FPT. Voorhees would like both matters to tag along. Court will continue bond on 16CM105 and will set for another FPT. Defendant states that he has no permanent address but could stay with a friend in Antigo. Court - bond - $500.00 cash with same conditions, sets for FPT.
